Description: An antique Egyptian stone with an arched top, depicting figures and hieroglyphics; in the collection of Dr. John Lee at the Hartwell Museum. 1835 Lithograph
Producer name: Print made by: G E Madeley
Acquisition notes: This is one of the 'six lithographic impressions from Egyptian antiquities' in the printed 'List of additions made to the collections in the British Museum in the year 1835' as a gift of Dr John Lee.
